  <Placemark>
   <name>Marine Weather Statement issued September 20 at 2:10AM AKDT by NWS Juneau AK</name>
   <styleUrl>#sev_minor</styleUrl>
   <Style>
    <BalloonStyle />
   </Style>
   <Snippet>Early Saturday morning scattered thunderstorms will likely move
over the southern inner channels associated with a frontal
passage. While lightning is possible, and heavy rainfall, the main
threat is gusty and erratic winds up to 35 knots as the front and
associated cells move across the southern inner waters early
Saturday morning. Anticipate a wind shift from the southeast,
becoming more southwesterly.</Snippet>
